Welcome to joetoo's dev-sbc/reflash_rp2

please use the provided template .conf files to create your own configs

note that the eselect module will allow you to select from among any
config file whose name begins "reflash_rp2_" and ends ".conf"

the reflash_rp2 script provided with this package will default to
"PRETEND" mode (display config but don't execute) and it has two ${command}
execution modes --
"list" - (default) list the *.uf2 files under the ${IMAGE_TREE} path selected by reflash_rp2.conf
"flash" - chosen by use of the commandline option f|f (flash)

Note:  "flash" will mount the RP2040 in usb-storage mode and copy the ${PROGRAM} selected
by reflash_rp2.conf to the RP2040, and then it will un-mount the mountpoint

See documentation at:
 https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/User:Brendlefly62/Radxa_x4_N100_sbc_with_RP2040/Use_the_RP2040_Microcontroller#Copy_the_program_to_the_rp2040
Which also references:
